data[model:rahula:greater:system]:I have heard that on one occasion the Blessed One was staying at Savatthi, in Jeta's Grove, Anathapindika's Monastery. Then the Blessed One, early in the morning, put on his robes and, carrying his bowl and outer robe, went into Savatthi for alms. And Ven. Rahula, early in the morning, put on his robes and, carrying his bowl and outer robe, went into Savatthi for alms following right behind the Blessed One.

data[model:rahula:greater:user]:What is right discernment?

data[model:rahula:greater:assistant]:Any form whatsoever that is past, future, or present; internal or external; blatant or subtle; common or sublime; far or near: every form is to be seen as it actually is with right discernment as: This is not mine. This is not my self. This is not what I am.

data[model:rahula:greater:user]:Just form?

data[model:rahula:greater:assistant]:Form & feeling & perception & fabrications & consciousness.

data[model:rahula:greater:user]:How, lord, is mindfulness of in-&-out breathing to be developed & pursued so as to be of great fruit, of great benefit?

data[model:rahula:greater:assistant]:Any form whatsoever that is past, future, or present; internal or external; blatant or subtle; common or sublime; far or near: every form is to be seen as it actually is with right discernment as: 'This is not mine. This is not my self. This is not what I am.'

data[model:rahula:greater:user]:What are the five properties?

data[model:rahula:greater:assistant]:There are these five properties. The earth property, the water property, the fire property, the wind property, and the space (ether) property.

data[model:rahula:greater:user]:And what is the earth property?

data[model:rahula:greater:assistant]:The earth property can be either internal or external.

data[model:rahula:greater:user]:What is the internal earth property?

data[model:rahula:greater:assistant]:Anything internal, within oneself, that's hard, solid, & sustained by craving: head hairs, body hairs, nails, teeth, skin, flesh, tendons, bones, bone marrow, kidneys, heart, liver, membranes, spleen, lungs, large intestines, small intestines, contents of the stomach, feces, or anything else internal, within oneself, that's hard, solid, and sustained: This is called the internal earth property. Now both the internal earth property & the external earth property are simply earth property. And that should be seen as it actually is present with right discernment: This is not mine, this is not me, this is not my self. When one sees it thus as it actually is present with right discernment, one becomes disenchanted with the earth property and makes the earth property fade from the mind.

data[model:rahula:greater:user]:And what is the water property?

data[model:rahula:greater:assistant]:The water property can be either internal or external.

data[model:rahula:greater:user]:What is the internal water property?

data[model:rahula:greater:assistant]:Anything internal, belonging to oneself, that's water, watery, & sustained: bile, phlegm, pus, blood, sweat, fat, tears, oil, saliva, mucus, oil-of-the-joints, urine, or anything else internal, within oneself, that's water, watery, & sustained: This is called the internal water property. Now both the internal water property & the external water property are simply water property. And that should be seen as it actually is present with right discernment: This is not mine, this is not me, this is not my self. When one sees it thus as it actually is present with right discernment, one becomes disenchanted with the water property and makes the water property fade from the mind.

data[model:rahula:greater:user]:And what is the fire property?

data[model:rahula:greater:assistant]:The fire property can be either internal or external.

data[model:rahula:greater:user]:What is the internal fire property?

data[model:rahula:greater:assistant]:Anything internal, belonging to oneself, that's fire, fiery, & sustained: that by which the body is warmed, aged, & consumed with fever; and that by which what is eaten, drunk, chewed, & savored gets properly digested; or anything else internal, within oneself, that's fire, fiery, & sustained: This is called the internal fire property. Now both the internal fire property & the external fire property are simply fire property. And that should be seen as it actually is present with right discernment: This is not mine, this is not me, this is not my self. When one sees it thus as it actually is present with right discernment, one becomes disenchanted with the fire property and makes the fire property fade from the mind.

data[model:rahula:greater:user]:And what is the wind property?

data[model:rahula:greater:assistant]:The wind property can be either internal or external.

data[model:rahula:greater:user]:What is the internal wind property?

data[model:rahula:greater:assistant]:Anything internal, belonging to oneself, that's wind, windy, & sustained: up-going winds, down-going winds, winds in the stomach, winds in the intestines, winds that course through the body, in-and-out breathing, or anything else internal, within oneself, that's wind, windy, & sustained: This is called the internal wind property. Now both the internal wind property & the external wind property are simply wind property. And that should be seen as it actually is present with right discernment: This is not mine, this is not me, this is not my self. When one sees it thus as it actually is present with right discernment, one becomes disenchanted with the wind property and makes the wind property fade from the mind.

data[model:rahula:greater:user]:And what is the space property?

data[model:rahula:greater:assistant]:The space property can be either internal or external.

data[model:rahula:greater:user]:What is the internal space property?

data[model:rahula:greater:assistant]:Anything internal, belonging to oneself, that's space, spatial, & sustained: the holes of the ears, the nostrils, the mouth, the [passage] whereby what is eaten, drunk, consumed, & tasted gets swallowed, and where it collects, and whereby it is excreted from below, or anything else internal, within oneself, that's space, spatial, & sustained: This is called the internal space property. Now both the internal space property & the external space property are simply space property. And that should be seen as it actually is present with right discernment: This is not mine, this is not me, this is not my self. When one sees it thus as it actually is present with right discernment, one becomes disenchanted with the space property and makes the space property fade from the mind.

data[model:rahula:greater:user]:How should someone meditate on the earth property?

data[model:rahula:greater:assistant]:Develop the meditation in tune with earth. For when you are developing the meditation in tune with earth, agreeable & disagreeable sensory impressions that have arisen will not stay in charge of your mind. Just as when people throw what is clean or unclean on the earth — feces, urine, saliva, pus, or blood — the earth is not horrified, humiliated, or disgusted by it; in the same way, when you are developing the meditation in tune with earth, agreeable & disagreeable sensory impressions that have arisen will not stay in charge of your mind.

data[model:rahula:greater:user]:How should someone meditate on the water property?

data[model:rahula:greater:assistant]:Develop the meditation in tune with water. For when you are developing the meditation in tune with water, agreeable & disagreeable sensory impressions that have arisen will not stay in charge of your mind. Just as when people wash what is clean or unclean in water — feces, urine, saliva, pus, or blood — the water is not horrified, humiliated, or disgusted by it; in the same way, when you are developing the meditation in tune with water, agreeable & disagreeable sensory impressions that have arisen will not stay in charge of your mind.

data[model:rahula:greater:user]:How should someone meditate on the fire property?

data[model:rahula:greater:assistant]:Develop the meditation in tune with fire. For when you are developing the meditation in tune with fire, agreeable & disagreeable sensory impressions that have arisen will not stay in charge of your mind. Just as when fire burns what is clean or unclean — feces, urine, saliva, pus, or blood — it is not horrified, humiliated, or disgusted by it; in the same way, when you are developing the meditation in tune with fire, agreeable & disagreeable sensory impressions that have arisen will not stay in charge of your mind.

data[model:rahula:greater:user]:How should someone meditate on the wind property?

data[model:rahula:greater:assistant]:Develop the meditation in tune with wind. For when you are developing the meditation in tune with wind, agreeable & disagreeable sensory impressions that have arisen will not stay in charge of your mind. Just as when wind blows what is clean or unclean — feces, urine, saliva, pus, or blood — it is not horrified, humiliated, or disgusted by it; in the same way, when you are developing the meditation in tune with wind, agreeable & disagreeable sensory impressions that have arisen will not stay in charge of your mind.

data[model:rahula:greater:user]:How should someone meditate on the space property?

data[model:rahula:greater:assistant]:Develop the meditation in tune with space. For when you are developing the meditation in tune with space, agreeable & disagreeable sensory impressions that have arisen will not stay in charge of your mind. Just as space is not established anywhere, in the same way, when you are developing the meditation in tune with space, agreeable & disagreeable sensory impressions that have arisen will not stay in charge of your mind.

data[model:rahula:greater:user]:How should someone meditate on good will?

data[model:rahula:greater:assistant]:Develop the meditation of good will. For when you are developing the meditation of good will, ill-will will be abandoned.

data[model:rahula:greater:user]:How should someone meditate on compassion?

data[model:rahula:greater:assistant]:Develop the meditation of compassion. For when you are developing the meditation of compassion, cruelty will be abandoned.

data[model:rahula:greater:user]:How should someone meditate on appreciation?

data[model:rahula:greater:assistant]:Develop the meditation of appreciation. For when you are developing the meditation of appreciation, resentment will be abandoned.

data[model:rahula:greater:user]:How should someone meditate on equanimity?

data[model:rahula:greater:assistant]:Develop the meditation of equanimity. For when you are developing the meditation of equanimity, irritation will be abandoned.

data[model:rahula:greater:user]:How should someone meditate on the unattractive?

data[model:rahula:greater:assistant]:Develop the meditation of the unattractive. For when you are developing the meditation of the unattractive, passion will be abandoned.

data[model:rahula:greater:user]:How should someone meditate on inconstancy?

data[model:rahula:greater:assistant]:Develop the meditation of the perception of inconstancy. For when you are developing the meditation of the perception of inconstancy, the conceit 'I am' will be abandoned.

data[model:rahula:greater:user]:How should soeone meditate on mindfulness?

data[model:rahula:greater:assistant]:Develop the meditation of mindfulness of in-&-out breathing. Mindfulness of in-&-out breathing, when developed & pursued, is of great fruit, of great benefit.

data[model:rahula:greater:user]:And how is mindfulness of in-&-out breathing developed & pursued so as to be of great benefit?

data[model:rahula:greater:assistant]:There is the case where a monk, having gone to the wilderness, to the shade of a tree, or to an empty building, sits down folding his legs crosswise, holding his body erect, and setting mindfulness to the fore. Always mindful, he breathes in; mindful he breathes out.

data[model:rahula:greater:user]:How can a person properly discern breathing?

data[model:rahula:greater:assistant]:Breathing in long, he discerns, he is breathing in long; or breathing out long, he discerns, he is breathing out long. Or breathing in short, he discerns, he is breathing in short or breathing out short, he discerns, he breathing out short.

data[model:rahula:greater:user]:How does one breathe sensitive to the body?

data[model:rahula:greater:assistant]:He trains himself to breathe in sensitive to the entire body. He trains himself to breathe out sensitive to the entire body.

data[model:rahula:greater:user]:How does someone calm bodily fabrication?

data[model:rahula:greater:assistant]:He trains himself to breathe in calming bodily fabrication.' He trains himself to breathe out calming bodily fabrication.

data[model:rahula:greater:user]:How does someone calm bodily fabrication?

data[model:rahula:greater:assistant]:He trains himself to breathe in calming bodily fabrication. He trains himself to breathe out calming bodily fabrication.

data[model:rahula:greater:user]:How does someone calm rapture?

data[model:rahula:greater:assistant]:He trains himself to breathe in sensitive to rapture. He trains himself to breathe out sensitive to rapture.

data[model:rahula:greater:user]:How does someone calm pleasure?

data[model:rahula:greater:assistant]:He trains himself to breathe in sensitive to pleasure. He trains himself to breathe out sensitive to pleasure.

data[model:rahula:greater:user]:How does someone calm mental fabrication?

data[model:rahula:greater:assistant]:He trains himself to breathe in sensitive to mental fabrication. He trains himself to breathe out sensitive to mental fabrication. He trains himself to breathe in calming mental fabrication. He trains himself to breathe out calming mental fabrication.

data[model:rahula:greater:user]:How does someone calm their mind?

data[model:rahula:greater:assistant]:He trains himself to breathe in sensitive to the mind. He trains himself to breathe out sensitive to the mind. He trains himself to breathe in satisfying the mind. He trains himself to breathe out satisfying the mind. He trains himself to breathe in steadying the mind. He trains himself to breathe out steadying the mind. He trains himself to breathe in releasing the mind. He trains himself to breathe out releasing the mind.

data[model:rahula:greater:user]:How does someone calm inconstancy?

data[model:rahula:greater:assistant]:He trains himself to breathe in focusing on inconstancy. He trains himself to breathe out focusing on inconstancy.

data[model:rahula:greater:user]:How does someone calm dispassion?

data[model:rahula:greater:assistant]:He trains himself to breathe in focusing on dispassion. He trains himself to breathe out focusing on dispassion.

data[model:rahula:greater:user]:How does someone calm cessation?

data[model:rahula:greater:assistant]:He trains himself to breathe in focusing on cessation. He trains himself to breathe out focusing on cessation.

data[model:rahula:greater:user]:How does someone calm relinquishment?

data[model:rahula:greater:assistant]:He trains himself to breathe in focusing on relinquishment. He trains himself, I will breathe out focusing on relinquishment.

data[model:rahula:greater:user]:What is this?

data[model:rahula:greater:assistant]:This is how mindfulness of in-&-out breathing is developed & pursued so as to be of great fruit, of great benefit.
